    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Transparent, dark brown pigment made by roasting green earth to produce a warmer color. Transparent brown is a permanent pigment that is used primarily for glazing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種天然的棕色黏土顏料，含有鐵、錳氧化物、矽石、礬土和石灰，顏色沒有赭土那麼橘紅。此詞彙之英文umber意指義大利的翁布里亞區（Umbria），不過世界上還有其它地方能找到此顏料，特別是塞普勒斯。棕土自史前時代即被當作顏料使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
